  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Project requirements specify that relative hemolysis index RH < 1 must be demonstrated across all five flow-speed combinations; these requirements informed factor scoping and acceptance criteria throughout the assessment.",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cou1-hemolysis-credibility",
